-- Serena Williams Takes First Set Against Czech Kvitova in Wimbledon Match
-- James Cone
-- 2010-07-01T15:14:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/serena-williams-wins-first-set-vs-kvitova-in-wimbledon-semifinal.html

          
          
             Defending champion Serena Williams
won the opening set 7-6 (7-5) against Petra Kvitova in their
Wimbledon semifinal today.  
 The 28-year-old American won this year’s Australian Open
to secure her 12th Grand Slam title, a haul that includes three
Wimbledon championships.  
 Kvitova of the Czech Republic had previously never been
beyond the first round at Wimbledon and is playing in a first
Grand Slam semifinal.  
 The winner will face Russia’s Vera Zvonareva  
          
          


  


        